        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 11:50PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 1150 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
near Lodge Grass, or 29 miles southeast of Hardin, moving northeast
at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lodge Grass, Busby, Northern Cheyenne Indian Reservation and Crow
Indian Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
